However, women sometimes use a divorce as a weapon to manipulate a divorce to their own gain. For example, in the Netherlands, men may be ordered to pay alimony if a divorce is not granted to them, and the average divorce in the Netherlands costs over $6,000.

About half of the Dutch population lives in a house which has an obsolete or small kitchen. Less than 56% of Dutch people say that they cook every day, and 45% state that they are not particularly concerned about their weight. About 50% of Dutch households in the Netherlands do not own a vacuum cleaner, which is considered an unclean asset. and 77% of Dutch households say that they spend a lot of time in a car each month.
